docs.text: one stormy night during the summer of 1839 , the 53 men imprisoned on the spanish slave ship la amistad escape .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: led by the lion-hearted cinque ( djimon hounsou ) , they take control of the vessel , killing most of the crew .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: adrift somewhere off the coast of cuba and uncertain how to make their way back to africa , they rely on the two surviving spaniards to navigate the eastward journey .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: they are tricked , however , and the la amistad , which makes its way northward off the united states' eastern coastline , is eventually captured by an american naval ship near connecticut .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the kidnapped africans are shackled and thrown into prison , charged with murder and piracy .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the first men to come to the africans' defense are abolitionists theodore joadson ( morgan freeman ) and lewis tappan ( stellan skarsgard ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: they are soon joined by roger baldwin ( matthew mcconaughey ) , a property attorney of little repute .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: aided by advice from former president john quincy adams ( anthony hopkins ) , baldwin proves a more persuasive orator than anyone gave him credit for , and his central argument -- that the prisoners were illegally kidnapped free men , not property -- convinces the judge .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but powerful forces have aligned against baldwin's cause .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: current president martin van buren ( nigel hawthorne ) , eager to please southern voters and 11-year old queen isabella of spain ( anna paquin ) , begins pulling strings behind-the-scenes to ensure that none of the africans goes free .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: at its heart , amistad is a tale of human courage .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: cinque is a heroic figure whose spirit remains unbreakable regardless of the pain and indignity he is subjected to .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he is a free man , not a slave , and , while he recognizes that he may die as a result of his struggle , he will not give it up .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: effectively portrayed by newcomer djimon hounsou , whose passion and screen presence arrest our attention , cinque is the key to viewers seeing the amistad africans as more than symbols in a battle of ideologies .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: they are individuals , and our ability to make that distinction is crucial to the movie's success .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: to amplify this point , spielberg presents many scenes from the africans' point-of-view , detailing their occasionally-humorous observations about some of the white man's seemingly-strange " rituals " .

docs.text: the larger struggle is , of course , one of defining humanity .

docs.text: as the nazis felt justified in slaughtering jews because they viewed their victims as " sub-human , " so the pro-slavery forces of amistad use a similar defense .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the abolitionists regard the africans as men , but the slavers and their supporters see them as animals or property .

docs.text: in a sense , the morality of slavery is on trial here with the specter of civil war , which would break out less than three decades later , looming over everything .

docs.text: amistad's presentation of the legal and political intricacies surrounding the trial are fascinating , making this movie one of the most engrossing courtroom dramas in recent history .

docs.text: four claimants come forward against the africans : the state , which wants them tried for murder ; the queen of spain , who wants them handed over to her under the provision of an american/spanish treaty ; two american naval officers , who claim the right of high seas salvage ; and the two surviving spaniards from la amistad , who demand that their property be returned to them .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: even though attorney and client are divided by a language barrier , they gradually learn to communicate .

docs.text: finally , there's anthony hopkins , whose towering portrayal of john quincy adams is as compelling as anything the great actor has recently done .

docs.text: one point of difference worth noting between amistad and schindler's list is this film's lack of a well-defined human villain .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: schindler's list had ralph fiennes' superbly-realized amon goeth , who was not only a three-dimensional character , but a personification of all that the nazis stood for .

docs.text: there is no such figure in amistad .

docs.text: the villain is slavery , but an ideology , no matter how evil , is rarely the best adversary .

docs.text: it is to spielberg's credit that he has fashioned such a compelling motion picture without a prominent antagonist .
